Chelsea won 4-3 on penalties after a 1-1 draw against Aston Villa at the Stamford Bridge on Wednesday night. Much-maligned German forward Timo Werner headed Chelsea into the lead in the 54th minute, finishing off Reece James’ cross for his first goal in 11 games. Also Read: Mane, Salah Score To Lift Liverpool Over C’Palace With Villa fan Prince William watching from the stands, 19-year-old striker Cameron Archer equalised in the 64th minute with a close-range header from Matty Cash’s cross. Defender, James scored Chelsea’s winning penalty in the shoot-out after Ashley Young and Marvelous Nakamba missed for Villa.